%N A116115 Numbers k such that k concatenated with k-6 gives the product of two numbers which differ by 1.
%C A116115 If k-6 has d digits, the concatenation is k//k-6 = 10^d*k+k-6 = m*(m+1), therefore k//k-8 = 10^d*k+k-8 = (m-1)*(m+2), so there is a large overlap or equality with A116103. - _R. J. Mathar_, May 22 2026
%e A116115 58//52 = 76 * 77, where // denotes concatenation.
%Y A116115 Cf. A116101, A116103, A116116, A116120, A116246.
